<HEADLINE> Vietnam Voices Concern over U.S. Air Strikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam has expressed great
concern and regret over U.S. air strikes on sites in Afghanistan
and Sudan suspected to be involved in recent terrorist activities.
</P>
<P>
"Vietnam disapproves of any international terrorist acts," a
Foreign Ministry spokesman said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. military actions, the spokesman noted, not only caused
great losses to innocent people, but also might trigger more
violence, jeopardizing regional and global peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
"All international anti-terrorist activities must respect
international laws and the independence and sovereignty of all
nations," the spokesman added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
