<HEADLINE> German Leader Supports Russian Anti-Crisis Measures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 22 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl on
Saturday expressed support for the anti-crisis measures taken by
the Russian government, the Russian presidential press service
said.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone conversation with Russian President Boris
Yeltsin, Kohl expressed satisfaction with Russia's reiteration of
its obligations with regard to foreign debt, the Itar-Tass news
agency quoted the press service as saying.
</P>
<P>
The phone call came days after the Russian government and
central bank devalued the ruble and imposed a 90-day moratorium on
repayment of foreign debts at the beginning of the week.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also talked about such international issues as
Kosovo and the situation on the world financial markets in their
lengthy conversation, the service said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin made similar calls on Thursday to French President
Jacques and Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
