<HEADLINE> Missing Plane in Nepal Still Not Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The rescue teams including
four helicopters on Saturday could not track the passenger plane
which has lost contact since Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Bad weather blocked the smooth operation of the searching work,
the official RSS news agency said, adding that the helicopters
will resume the search operation early Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
The army and police have been joining in the operation as well.
</P>
<P>
Radio Nepal said that the Indian Search and Rescue Organization
has been requested to help track the plane through satellite.
</P>
<P>
The plane with 18 people on board including three crew members
and three Indians lost contact five minutes after it took off at
11:10 am Friday in Jomsom, western Nepal.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which belongs to the private-owned Lumbini Airways,
was scheduled to fly to Pokhara, just 80 kilometres away. 
</P>
</TEXT>
