<HEADLINE> UAE Renews Condemnation of Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 22 (Xinhua) -- In its first official reaction
to the bombings of the two U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania,
the United Arab Emirates condemns all forms of terrorism on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A UAE Foreign Ministry official, who spoke on customary
practice of anonymity, told reporters that his country calls on
the U.N. Security Council to shoulder its responsibility and adopt
appropriate anti-terrorist measures.
</P>
<P>
The UAE also calls on the international community to take
urgent and collective moves through the Security Council to uproot
terrorism and define the responsibility of the countries that
support the terrorist organizations, the official added.
</P>
<P>
The official concluded by saying that the UAE expresses time
BAP371PAB137I22TFQL02:3402:341601
and again its deep belief that terrorism is a grave phenomenon
which is utterly alien to the tolerant and merciful Islam.
</P>
<P>
The remarks of the UAE official followed the U.S. air raids on
suspected terrorist-related sites in Sudan and Afghanistan on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. missile strikes were a retaliatory measure against the
August 7 bombings of the U.S. embassies in Kenya and
Tanzania. More than 250 people were killed and 5,000 others
injured in the bombing attacks. 
</P>
