<HEADLINE> Jordan's Regent Voices Support for Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan,
the Regent said Saturday that Jordan will continue its support for
the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
This is the first remark the regent made on the issue of the
Palestinians since King Hussein temporarily transferred most of
his rights to Hassan on August 12.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the cabinet members and some parliament deputies,
Hassan said Jordan has a "commitment towards the Palestinians to
achieve their legitimate rights on their national soil."
</P>
<P>
His remarks are totally in line with Hussein's policy on the
Palestinian issue.
</P>
<P>
The power transfer has been the first one in Hussein's ruling
history. It happened after the king had to stay in the United
States for a long period of time to treat the cancer in his
lymphatic tissue.
</P>
<P>
Jordan has been keeping a close watch on the developments of
the Israeli-Palestinian peace process. It supports the
Palestinians to establish an independent state with its capital in
Jerusalem, while it sticks to a policy of normalizing ties with
the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
Jordan is now Israel's closest ally in the Arab world. And it
is one of the two Arab countries to have reached peace treaty with
Israel. 
</P>
