Defense Oumar Kedgelani and Maman Sidikou, the Nigerien Minister
of Foreign Affairs and African Integration, the Nigerian TV
Authority (NTA) said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The committee will work out a frame work for joint military
operations to combat criminal activities along their borders,
said a communique signed in Nigerian capital Abuja Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The three countries decided to vigorously prosecute all
criminals arrested in any of the states.
</P>
<P>
According to the communique, regular meetings between heads of
various administrative units at state and local governments, as
well as traditional rulers, will be convened to monitor security
situation in the said area.
</P>
<P>
The meeting came on heel of a mini-summit attended by leaders
of the three countries on regional issues on August 12.
</P>
<P>
In a communique signed at the end of their meeting, the
leaders expressed their concern over the threat to peace,
security and stability posed by the activities of rebels, bandits
and other undesirable elements in the Lake Chad area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
