<HEADLINE> Iranian President Orders Release of 84 Prisoners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami has ordered the release of 84 prisoners jailed for
defaulting on debts.
</P>
<P>
The presidential office has agreed to pay the debts of the
prisoners which range from 35,000 (about 6.4 U.S. dollars) to
seven million rials (about 1,273 dollars), the official Islamic
Republic News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
All these prisoners, including six women, are jailed in the
southwestern province of Khuzestan.
</P>
<P>
Khatami visited the province in February and the families of
the inmates appealed to him to help release them.
</P>
<P>
The amnesty came on the eve of the Government Week which starts
on August 24.
</P>
<P>
The Government Week marks the death anniversary of the
former Iranian President Mohammad Ali Rajaie and Prime Minister
Mohammad Javad Bahonar, who were killed in a bomb explosion
allegedly by the Iranian outlawed Mujaheddin Khalq Organization
on August 30, 1981. 
</P>
