<HEADLINE> Hurricane Bonnie Threatening Southeast U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Hurricane Bonnie is
threatening southeastern United States as storm gathered strength
over the open Atlantic after striking southern Bahamas on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Bonnie, which acquired hurricane strength early on Saturday, is
expected to become a major hurricane, with winds from 180 to 210
kilometers per hour within two days.
</P>
<P>
At 2 p.m. EDT (1800 GMT), the center of Bonnie was about 240
kilometers north-northeast of Turk Island in the Turks and Caicos
chain at latitude 23 north, longitude 70.5 west.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to grow to a Category 3 hurricane with top winds
of 180 to 210 kph and take a gradual turn to the northwest,
skirting the Florida coast. 
</P>
