Biaggi took over the No. 1 in the overall standings after
winning the 22-lap race.
</P>
<P>
Doohan slid off the track in a late turn during the first lap
but continued his race after remounted his Honda.
</P>
<P>
He had to quit after 13 laps, as an exhaust pipe bent in the
crash was burning through his racing leathers.
</P>
<P>
Doohan slipped to third in the standings, 13 points behind
Biaggi and two behind Spain's Alex Criville, who finished second
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Alex Barros of Brazil was third, completing a sweep of the
first three places for Honda.
</P>
