<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Full Text of Message of Jiang Zemin to Rehabilitation Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A message from Chinese
President Jiang Zemin was read by Deng Pufang, chairman of the
China Disabled Persons' Federation, at the opening ceremony of the
11th Rehabilitation International Asia and the Pacific Regional
Conference here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The full text of the message is as follows:
</P>
<P>
The 11th Rehabilitation International Asia and the Pacific
Regional Conference,
</P>
<P>
On the occasion of the convening of the 11th Rehabilitation
International Asia and the Pacific Regional Conference cum the
Campaign '98 for the Asian and Pacific Decade of Disabled Persons
(1993-2002) in Hong Kong, I would like to express, on behalf of
the Chinese government and people as well as in my own name, warm
congratulations to the conference and good wishes to all delegates
and participants!
</P>
<P>
It is of special significance for Hong Kong to host this
conference after her return to the motherland. Friends from all
over the world could witness the successful practice in Hong Kong
of the Chinese government's policies of "one country, two
systems", "Hong Kong people administrating Hong Kong affairs" and
high degree of autonomy, and could feel the efforts of the Chinese
government and the government of Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region to promote the general progress of social civilization
along with their dedication to economic development.
</P>
<P>
Disability exists along with human beings. People with
disabilities have the desire and ability to participate in
community life and are equally creators of social wealth for which
they make much greater efforts than people without disabilities.
They, as all others, should be entitled to all human dignity and
rights. The emancipation of disabled people as the most
under-privileged group in the society symbolizes significantly the
development of human civilization and social progress.
</P>
<P>
The 48th Session of the UNESCAP held in Beijing in April, 1992
adopted unanimously the resolution, proclaiming 1993-2002 as the
Asian and Pacific Decade of Disabled Persons. Such an effort and
that of Rehabilitation International for improving rehabilitation
service to disabled people expresses the lofty pursuit of the
international community for further improving the status of
disabled people and giving more play to their roles in society.
The convening of this conference will make new contribution to the
promotion of the undertaking of disabled people.
</P>
<P>
By following the United Nations World Program concerning
Disabled Persons and the ESCAP resolution on the Asian and Pacific
Decade of Disabled Persons, the Chinese government has adopted
many effective measures in light with the specific situation of
her disabled people to protect the rights and interest of disabled
people. China promulgated the Law on the Protection of Disabled
People, formulated and are implementing three consecutive 5-year
work programs for promoting work on disability, support the
establishment of organizations of disabled people, encourage the
self-efforts by disabled people, all of which have remarkably
changed and improved the status of disabled people in the aspects
of rehabilitation, education, employment as well as material and
cultural life.
</P>
<P>
China takes a considerable portion in the world population with
disabilities. The Chinese government and people are willing to
work together with the international community and share our
efforts for realizing the goals of "equality, participating and
sharing" of disabled people and for our endeavor of human
civilization and progress!
</P>
<P>
I wish the conference success!
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
