<HEADLINE> 1stld Writethru: Iran's Former Chief Prosecutor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Former head of Iran's Prisons
Organization Assadollah Lajevardi, his brother and a passer-by
were assassinated Sunday morning by two armed assailants at his
business office in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The two gunmen entered Lajevardi's office at Tehran's grand
bazaar and shot him dead, the official news agency IRNA reported.
Lajevardi's brother and a passer-by who tried to stop the
assailants from fleeing were also killed.
</P>
<P>
One of the assailants was arrested. The bodies of the victims
were transferred from the shop, where Lajevardi and his brother
were doing their business, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Police cordoned off the bazaar, the capital's traditional
marketplace, shortly after the attack, and started investigation
of the motives behind the assassination.
</P>
<P>
Lajevardi, 63, had "a bright record of services" for the
Islamic Revolution both before and after its victory in 1979, IRNA
said. He joined the revolution when he was young and became a
confidant of the late spiritual leader Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini.
</P>
<P>
Once a prisoner in the late shah's regime, Lajevardi was asked
to administer the Prisons Organization after the establishment of
the Islamic Republic in 1979.
</P>
<P>
He supported Majlis (parliament) Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri
in last year's presidential election, in which the speaker
failed. He resigned las year and returned to the same business he
did in the bazaar before the revolution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
