<HEADLINE> Companies to Take Part in HK Sports Carnival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Employees from Hong Kong's
253 companies are to have the most fun in a sport carnival which
started on Sunday and would last for months.
</P>
<P>
A historical number of entries are taking part in the
four-month-long tournament of the Corporate Games 1998, which
were kicked off on Sunday here at the Wai Tsuen Indoor Recreation
Center.
</P>
<P>
A total of 18 competitions were featured in the tournament
which is jointly organized by the Provisional Urban Council (PUC)
and Provisional Regional Council (Pro RC).
</P>
<P>
Wong King-cheung, chairman of the PUC's Sports and Activities
Sub-Committee, said on Sunday's opening ceremony that the
tournament is one of the major programs organized by the two
provisional municipal councils to promote the "Sport-for-all"
concept.
</P>
<P>
"It's beyond a pure sport competition," said Chan Ping,
chairman of the Pro RC's Recreation and Sports Select Committee.
"The companies could benefit from more communication with their
employees and more responsibility of the employees through the
tournament."
</P>
<P>
Contenders will compete in table tennis, seven-a-side
mini-soccer, tennis, squash, snooker, track and field, swimming,
angling, orienteering, lawn bowls, water carnival, basketball,
ten-pin bowling, badminton, beach volleyball, soccer, long
distance running and fun games in the games which end on December.
</P>
<P>
Besides individual titles, a company which accumulates the
highest score in the overall 18 events will snatch the
corporation trophy.
</P>
<P>
The winner company could keep the trophy forever if it wins
for three consecutive years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
