<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Students Given Beijing University Degrees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A total of 139 undergraduate and
graduate students from Hong Kong were given degrees today for a
joint program of Beijing University and Hong Kong's Shue Yan
College.
</P>
<P>
The students were given the Beijing University graduation
certificates by the president of Beijing University, Chen Jia'er,
and the head of the Hong Kong college, Chung Chi Yung.
</P>
<P>
There were 116 bachelor's degrees and 20 master's degrees. The
Hong Kong college has been providing these joint courses in law,
economics, literature, and history for 11 years. The project has
had more than 2,500 undergrads and more than 300 grad students,
who have gotten 555 bachelor and 100 master degrees from Beijing
University.
</P>
<P>
Vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference Luo Haocai attended today's ceremony. 
