<HEADLINE> China's Leaders And Flood Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese leaders Li Peng and Li
Ruihuan recently spoke with leaders of the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region about the battle against flooding there.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, who is Chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee, spoke by phone with them on Saturday evening
and praised soliders and policemen for their contribution to the
fight and said that the flood battle must be won by implementing
President Jiang Zemin's instructions.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, who is Chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee, spoke by phone
with Inner Mongolian officials while he was visiting other
flood-damaged provinces in central and east China.
</P>
<P>
Li visited the city of Jiujiang in Jiangxi Province on Saturday
and Yueyang in Hunan Province on Sunday and praised the work of
plugging a 60-meter breach in Yangtze River embankments in
Jiujiang by thousands of soliders.
</P>
<P>
He asked local government to give priority to preventing the
spread of epidemic diseases in flood-hit areas and said that flood
victims need to be provided with sufficient food, drinking water,
clothing, housing and medical care. 
</P>
