<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980823.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bazan Retains WBC Lightweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Cesar Bazan of
Mexico fought back the challenge from Japanese Hiroyuki Sakamoto
to retain his World Boxing Council (WBC) lightweight title Sunday
in Yokohama, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Bazan, 23, stretched his bout record to 33 wins, one draw and
two losses, including 23 knockouts.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican snatched the title from Steve Johnston of the
United States in June.
</P>
<P>
It was Sakamoto's second attempt for a world title following
his loss to Johnston in July last year.
</P>
<P>
The top-ranked Japanese contender in the WBC rankings stood
with 30 wins and three losses, including 22 knockouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
