<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Medical Team Arrives In Lhasa To Help Tibetans With Eye Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese medical team arrived in
the capital of Tibet Autonomous Region today to do eye operations
for some 1,000 Tibetans for free.
</P>
<P>
The project is a cooperative affair of the China Disabled
Persons Federation and Lions Clubs International, with 23 doctors
performing cataract operations on Tibetan patients in Lhasa and in
Qamdo, Nyingchi and Shannan prefectures.
</P>
<P>
A China Disabled Persons Federation spokesperson says that this
will be the first large scale cataract operation ever in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The incidence of cataracts in Tibet is double that of other
parts of China because of the high elevation and extreme exposure
to the sun's ultraviolet rays.
</P>
<P>
The underdeveloped economy and lack of access to medical and
communications services there make it almost impossible for
cataract sufferers to regain their eyesight.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
