<HEADLINE> 2.7 Billion Yuan In Donations For China's Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- China's flood victims have
gotten a response from Chinese and other people, who have given
2.7 billion yuan for flood stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
The donations consist of money and goods given to the Ministry
of Civil Affairs, China Charity Federation and China Red Cross
Society.
</P>
<P>
Donors include public servants, workers, farmers, enterprises,
private businessmen, overseas companies, Buddhists in Beijing who
sold off paintings and calligraphy works for the flood victims,
laid-off people, retired workers, and low-income families.
</P>
<P>
The eight democratic parties and All-China federation of
Industry and Commerce have collected more than 610,000 yuan
(73,000 U.S. dollars) in donations.
</P>
<P>
When the Hong Kong tycoon Li Ka-shing gave 50 million Hong Kong
dollars, some other Hong Kong tycoons followed suit as did many
other citizens. 
</P>
