<HEADLINE> Iran's Former Chief Prosecutor Assassinated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Former head of Iran's Prisons
Organization Assadollah Lajevardi was shot dead Sunday morning by
two assailants at his business office in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official news agency IRNA reported that the
unidentified gunmen entered Lajevardi's office at Tehran's grand
bazaar and talked with him.
</P>
<P>
But suddenly one of them opened fire at him with a Uzi machine
gun, and an elderly man who intervened was also shot dead, IRNA
quoted witnesses as saying.
</P>
<P>
One of the gunmen was arrested by the police.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the killing remained unclear.
</P>
<P>
Lajevardi, 63, a hardliner who supported Majlis (Parliament)
Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri in last year's presidential
elections, was a key figure in Iranian politics before the Islamic
Revolution in 1979. 
</P>
