<HEADLINE> Adult Education Prosperous in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- In addition to the development of
higher learning education, adult education in Macao has been
booming over the past dozen years, a government official said
during a two-day seminar on adult education which closed here
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
According to Chan Kai Chon, an official with the Education and
Youth Department of the Macao government, more than 80
institutions in Macao are engaged in adult education.
</P>
<P>
During the 1996-97 school year, nearly 47,000 people took adult
education courses of various kinds, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Adult education which lasts for people's entire life has
become the trend of adult-educational reform and development in
the world today, and such a trend is surely responded in Macao,"
the official said.
</P>
<P>
Among the adult educational institutions in Macao, less than
one-third are run by the government. Most of them are managed by
churches, social bodies and charitable or individual
organizations.
</P>
<P>
Major courses include language (including Portuguese, English
and Chinese), mathematics, accounting, computer, administration,
business management and other practical skills.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Sparetime Study Center, which was founded by the
Macao Federation of Trade Unions in 1982, is a major institution
on adult education in Macao.
</P>
<P>
The center was set up to help the large number of new
immigrants in Macao acquire better working skills, while Macao was
experiencing a fledgling economy at that time, said Lei Pui Lam,
president of the center.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 16 years, more than 81,000 persons have received
training at the center. That means one out of five Macao residents
is the center's beneficiary, Lei said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Macao government has been making concerted
efforts with social bodies and individuals in Macao to boost adult
education.
</P>
<P>
The government sets aside more than one million patacas (about
125,000 U.S. dollars) each year for adult education, according to
government sources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980823.0098 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
