<HEADLINE> Yangtze Water Levels Down Slowly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Water levels on the middle and
lower reaches of the Yangtze River has been dropping slowly for
the past 24 hours, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters told
Xinhua this afternoon that water levels fell to 43.67 metres in
Shashi of Hubei, 29.25 metres in Hankou of Hubei and 22.42 metres
in Jiujiang of Jiangxi as of 14:00 today, down by 0.04 to 0.23
metres, respectively, from Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Water level of the Dongting Lake at Chenglingji went down by
0.15 metres to 35.7 metres while water level of the Poyang Lake
fell by 0.03 metres to 21.84 metres.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, in northeast China, water levels of Nenjiang and
Songhua rivers registered a gradual fall upstream Harbin but
continued to rise downstream Harbin.
</P>
<P>
Water level of the Songhua River at Harbin has maintained at
120.89 metres since Saturday noon, 0.84 metres higher than the
previous record, according to the headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
