<HEADLINE> Floods in Sichuan Kill Nineteen, Three Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, August 23 (Xinhua) -- At least 19 people died in
flooding caused by torrential rains in Sichuan Province, in
southwest China, in recent days, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
Another three people were missing as some 35 counties of
Sichuan were hit by stormy rains between August 19 and 21,
according to the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
In Ziyang Prefecture which was hit hardest, 120 townships with
2.5 million local residents were rocked by the floods, with 15
people killed and three missing.
</P>
<P>
In Guangyuan City, ravaging floods affected seven counties, of
which three counties lost contact with the outside. Four local
residents died in the disaster.
</P>
<P>
Local governments and armed police forces have mobilized
emergency teams to the disaster-stricken areas. To date, residents
besieged by the floods have all been evacuated to safe places.
</P>
