<HEADLINE> Relief Supplies Reach Flooded Areas in Shortest Possible Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 23 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs
has managed to distribute the donated relief goods within the
shortest possible time.
</P>
<P>
An official with the ministry's disaster relief department said
the flood stricken areas urgently need cotton quilts, clean drink
water, pharmaceuticals and other necessary goods and his ministry
must ensure that the supplies reach the areas without any delay.
</P>
<P>
As soon as the donated goods sent to the ministry, public
servants there would connect with airport, railway and highway
administrative departments to confirm that the goods be delivered
the same day as they were received.
</P>
<P>
Hunan needs 1,586 tons of steel products. A provincial civil
affairs official on Friday rushed to the Beijing-based Shougang
Corporation which had promised to offer the steel products to the
flooded areas for help.
</P>
<P>
On the same day a transportation team set off for Hunan with
the steel products in various types Hunan needed.
</P>
<P>
The goods were expected to reach Hunan within three or four
days. In usual cases, such large amount of steel products would
reach Hunan in at least one week.
</P>
<P>
The official from Hunan also arranged a "train trip" within two
hours for 1,000 blankets donated for his province at the donation
center of the Ministry of Civil Affairs.
</P>
<P>
A few days ago, a batch of blankets, makeshift tents and water
purifiers donated by the United States government were sent to
Hunan by air. As soon as the plane landed the airport, big trucks
arranged by the provincial civil affairs department unloaded the
goods and sent them to the flooded areas immediately.  
</P>
</TEXT>
