<HEADLINE> Shanghai Records Rising Fixed Assets Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's fixed assets
investment topped 14.3 billion yuan (1.72 billion U.S. dollars)
in July, the highest monthly level for the year.
</P>
<P>
Some 7.6 billion yuan went for basic construction, up
50 percent on the corresponding month in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Local fixed assets investment fell 2.9 percent to 65.6 billion
yuan for the January-July period compared to the previous year's
period, with funds for urban infrastructure construction growing
by 37 percent to 20 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Some 19.9 billion yuan went for 45 local key projects set for
the year, with notable progress for automobile manufacturing,
metallurgical and transportation projects.
</P>
<P>
Investment in the Pudong New Area grew by 10 percent on the
1997 period to 19.8 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Pudong's industrial sector increased spending by a hefty 56
percent on the 1997 period, the figure for the transportation and
posts and telecommunications sectors was up by 21 percent and
spending for education and healthcare climbing by 82 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
