<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Local livestock producers are
asking the Philippine government to import 25,000 metric tons of
yellow corn on top of the proposed 300,000 metric tons for this
year.
</P>
<P>
Nemesio Co, chairman of the National Federation of Hog Farmers
Inc., said his group had made this request to the National Food
Authority, but has not yet received any reply, the Philippines
News Agency reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
