be needing the volume aside from the proposed 300,000 metric
tons," he said.
</P>
<P>
Co said the industry expects a supply shortfall of at least
200,000 metric tons despite the projected one-million-metric-ton
corn harvest next month.
</P>
<P>
"We (producers) evaluated whether there is a shortage or not.
We found out that definitely there is a shortage even during this
harvest season because this is only good for September and
October," he said.
</P>
<P>
Federation spokesman Francis Wong said it is also uncertain for
the producers to have good a corn harvest considering the El Nino
drought and the arrival of La Nina this year. 
