<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Calls for Single Standard on Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav Foreign Ministry
said Saturday that the Yugoslav Federal Republic firmly condemns
terrorism of all forms and that the international community must
fight terrorism by applying one unified single standard in
accordance with international law.
</P>
<P>
The ministry issued a statement in response to the U.S.
military strikes against alleged terrorist sites in Afghanistan
and Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The statement said Yugoslavia is of the view that it is
dangerous and unacceptable to apply double standards on
international terrorism.
</P>
<P>
It said that some people attempted to categorize international
terrorism as "good" and "bad." Toward those "good terrorists,"
they adopt a policy of protection, even deprive some sovereign
nations of their rights to fight terrorists on their own soil.
</P>
<P>
To those "bad terrorists," they adopt a policy of striking,
resorting to massive use of destructive weapons against the
territory of sovereign nations, even bypassing the Untied Nations
and violating the basic principles governing international
relations.
</P>
<P>
The statement concluded that Yugoslavia believes that the fight
against international terrorism must be carried out on the basis
of respect for the U.N. Charter and the sovereignty and
territorial integrity of nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
