<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, August 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING -- Chinese Insurance companies reacted quickly to
settle compensations claims arising from the the heavy floods
sweeping China Since July.
</P>
<P>
Today's Business Weekly of China Daily reported that the
People's Insurance Company of China Group (PICC Group) has
provided advance payments totalling 1 billion yuan (120 million
U.S. dollars) to the flood-hit areas by August 20.
(China-Insurers-Flood Victims)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- The Costa Rican coffee output may drop by some
200,000 46-kilo bags during the 1998-99 season, down 6.3 percent
from the 1997-98 figure. (Costa Rica-Coffee)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- The average price of the Venezuelan basket of crudes
and byproducts this week registered a slight increase of 15 cents
of a U.S. dollar to end at 9.83 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
According to the Mines and Energy Ministry, the VBC registered
so far this month an average of 10.07 dollars per barrel.
(Venezuela-Oil Price)
</P>
<P>
-- --
</P>
<P>
PRAGUE -- The Slovak foreign debts soared to 11.2 billion
U.S. dollars at the end of May this year, the highest since 1993
when the country gained independence, according to news reports
reaching here Saturday. (Slovakia-Foreign Debts) 
</P>
