<HEADLINE> Argentina Reaps Bumper Harvest of Crops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's agriculture
registered a bumper harvest in the 1997/98 season, according to
figures released by the Agriculture, Livestock, Fishing and Food
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Although floods caused by El Nino affected wheat, cotton and
rice crops, but the plethora of water was a bless for soybeans
and corn cultivations, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Wheat output in this season reached 14.74 million tons, a
little less than the previous season. Cotton output was 950,000
tons and rice output 961,000 tons, both less than the previous
harvests.
</P>
<P>
Soybeans and sorghum output, already harvested, reached 16.53
million and 3.87 million tons respectively, up 68 percent and 51
percent over the previous season.
</P>
<P>
Corn production is expected to reach 19.13 million tons, as
against 14.496 million tons of the previous season.
</P>
<P>
Sunflower output amounted to 5.24 million tons, a 4 percent
increase over the previous period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
