<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Province Planning International Glider Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 23 (Xinhua) -- A festival that combines a
gliding competition with sightseeing is scheduled for Sept 5-10 in
the city of Linzhou in China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 gliders from China and abroad will compete for a
gold medal at the 6-day festival, the organizing committee says,
and some 20 travel companies will organize events.
</P>
<P>
Linzhou, which is located in the northern part of Henan, has a
large water conservation project with channels hewn in stony
mountains, providing drinking water for local villagers.
</P>
<P>
This "Red Flag Channel" has become a popular sightseeing spot,
attracting thousands of visitors, according to the local tourism
bureau.  
</P>
