<HEADLINE> Tight Security Given to U.S. Embassy in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Tight security has been given to
the United States Embassy in Colombo following Thursday's U.S.
missile strikes on Afghanistan and Sudan, according to police
sources here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The embassy had not made a formal request but security has been
given to all important U.S. installations to avoid any
embarrassment, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the U.S. government has warned all Americans
worldwide that radical groups might launch fresh attacks against
U.S. targets in retaliation to its missile attacks on Afghanistan
and Sudan, the  sources added.
</P>
<P>
Washington on Thursday launched missile strikes on alleged
terrorist targets in Afghanistan and Sudan in response to the twin
bombings on August 7 in Kenya and Tanzania, which killed 257
people and injured more than 5,000 others. 
</P>
