<HEADLINE> Shenyang to Host International Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, capital of northeast
China's Liaoning Province, will host an international trade fair
between Sept 2-6.
</P>
<P>
Over 3,000 foreign businessmen will attend the fair which is
expected to attract foreign investment of some 1.5 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The fair will feature exhibits of over 100 projects in the
realm of science, environmental protection, energy,
infrastructure, agriculture and brand name products.
</P>
<P>
The China Council for the Promotion of International Trade
(CCPIT) will jointly sponsor the event with a number of cities,
including Shenyang, Anshan, Benxi, Dandong, Yingkou, Liaoyang and
Tieling in the province.
</P>
<P>
In the first seven months of this year, Shenyang approved 339
projects using foreign investment, with foreign investment
actually used amounting to nearly 400 million U.S. dollars, 13
percent higher than the same period of last year. 
</P>
