<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drug Abuse Among Thai Youth Found Escalating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 23 (Xinhua) -- Drug abuse among Thai Youth has
sharply escalated with twice as many trials held this year than
the previous year, according to the Central and Juvenile Court.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year 9,506 youths have been tried,
close to the number of 10,286 tried in the whole last year, Vicha
Mahakum, Deputy Chief of the court was quoted Sunday by The Nation
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Of the drug-related offenses this year, 80 percent of the
youths were charged with drug abuse and 20 percent of selling
illegal drugs, Vicha said.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, amphetamine has gone ahead of heroin, which had
always been popular among the young people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
