(about 322,000 dollars) for Slovakia in its relief aid to the
neighboring country.
</P>
<P>
Eastern Slovakia was hit hard by torrential rains and floods in
late July. About 48 people were reported killed in the floods,
more than 40 missing and thousands of others were rendered
homeless. Direct economic losses were estimated at exceeding 2
billion Koruna (about 64 million U.S. dollars). 
