<DOCNO> XIE19980823.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dominican Republic, Caricom Sign Free Trade Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Dominican Republic and the
Caribbean Community (Caricom) signed a free trade agreement
Saturday, according to reports from Santo Domingo.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, which was signed during the meeting of the
Caribbean Forum, favors the elimination of non-tariff barriers to
commerce, establishes a system of rules of origin, customs
cooperation, and harmonizes technical and sanitary procedures.
</P>
<P>
It also promotes a gradual liberalization of the services, the
movement of capital, and the protection of investments directed
to strengthen competitivity.
</P>
<P>
It encourages the participation of private economic agents
to deepen and expand economic relations.
</P>
<P>
The areas to be most benefited are agriculture, mining,
industry, construction, tourism, transports, telecommunications,
banking, insurance, market of capital, professional services, and
science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, according to some experts, will benefit the
exchange of some 8,000 articles, aiming at discouraging
anti-competitive practices among involved parties.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is expected to strengthen the commercial and
economic relations, as well as the expansion of sale of goods in
the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
