<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Prices Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The average price of the
Venezuelan basket of crudes (VBC) and byproducts this week
registered a slight increase of 15 cents of a U.S. dollar to end
at 9.83 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
According to the Mines and Energy Ministry, the VBC registered
so far this month an average of 10.07 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) basket
of seven crudes closed Friday with an average of 11.74 dollars per
barrel.
</P>
<P>
To shore up the depressed oil prices, Venezuela has promoted a
global strategy of reduction of exports and agreed to reduce its
daily output to a total of 525,000 barrels a day until June 30,
1999.
</P>
<P>
The drastic drop of oil prices in the international markets and
the cuts in oil output have affected Venezuelan earnings which are
expected to lose more than 5 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Energy and Mines Minister Erwin Arrieta said Friday that his
country will not make more adjustments to its crude production.
</P>
<P>
"The production cuts have already been adopted and no more cuts
are planned," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
