<HEADLINE> Optical Fiber Connects Tibet with Chinese Inland Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 23 (Xinhua) -- An optical fiber project linking
southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region with Gansu and Qinghai
provinces in the northwest recently commenced operations some 25
days ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The 2,754-km telecommunications line links the Gansu capital of
Lanzhou with the Tibet capital of Lhasa, via Xining, capital of
Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
The project, completed at a cost of 612 million yuan, sits at
an average 4,000 meters above sea level and traverses 23
counties, cities and prefectures.
</P>
<P>
The telecom line will significantly improve Tibet's
telecommunications capacity, according to the local posts and
telecommunications department.
</P>
<P>
Tibet plans to install over 7,000 telecommunications lines to
open links with more than 20 major cities throughout the country,
in addition to some 1,170 intraregional lines.
</P>
<P>
Contruction of the project started in June 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
