<HEADLINE> Seles Beats Hingis in du Maurier Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- American Monica Seles upset top
seed Martina Hingis of Switzerland 4-6, 6-3, 6-2 in the
semifinals of the du Maurier Open women's tennis tournament in
Montreal on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"I really started to play well as the match went on," the
24-year-old Seles said. "I actually think she was lucky to win
the first set ... Everything just went well for me today."
</P>
<P>
Seles, the fifth seed, has won the last three du Maurier
tournaments.
</P>
<P>
The second semifinal later Saturday had second seed Jana
Novotna of the Czech Republic taking on third seed Arantxa
Sanchez Vicario of Spain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
