<HEADLINE> Kohl Expresses Worry about Kosovo Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl
Saturday held a telephone conservations with Russian President
Boris Yeltsin and expressed worry about the escalation of violence
in Yugoslavia's province of Kosovo, a German government spokesman
said Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
During his half-an-hour telephone conservations with Yeltsin,
Kohl expressed particular worry about the sufferings of civilians
in the Kosovo conflict as well as the growing number of refugees
from that region.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed disappointment about the failure of the
Yugoslav government in particular in delivering their promises to
end the conflict.
</P>
<P>
In the telephone talks, the two leaders also discussed the
recent Russian financial crisis, with Kohl expressing the hope
that Russia could manage to restore investors' confidence as soon
as possible, the German spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Kohl also reiterated Germany's willingness to offer advice to
Moscow on issues such as taxation policy and bank supervision, but
he also stressed that it would depend on Russia itself to create
the preconditions for a long-term solution to the financial
crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
