<HEADLINE> Moeller and Haessler Quit National Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Andreas Moeller and Thomas
Haessler quit the German national soccer team on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Eight players have now quit since three-time World Cup
champion Germany was upset by Croatia in the quarterfinals in
France.
</P>
<P>
Team captain Juergen Klinsmann, Andreas Koepke, Juergen
Kohler, Lothar Matthaeus, Stefan Reuter and Olaf Thon have all
pulled out of the national team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
